"title": "8822: self-justification",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8822",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>A self-centred attitude by which people defend their actions and beliefs without reference to God. Scripture insists that the confidence and ultimate justification of believers lie with God, and condemns those who look elsewhere for these.</p>\n<h2>The impossibility of self-justification</h2>\n<h3>Self-justification is impossible before a holy God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job25:4\">JOB 25:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam6:20\">1SA 6:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal3:2\">MAL 3:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev6:17\">REV 6:17</a></p>\n<h3>Justification is achieved by God, not by people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:1-Rom5:2\">ROM 5:1–5:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom3:27-Rom3:30\">ROM 3:27–3:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal2:20-Gal2:21\">GAL 2:20–2:21</a></p>\n<h2>How self-justification occurs</h2>\n<h3>Self-justification occurs through ignoring God and his ways</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh9:16\">NEH 9:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke16:14-Luke16:15\">LUK 16:14–16:15</a></p>\n<h3>Self-justification occurs through pride</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:9-Luke18:14\">LUK 18:9–18:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt23:1-Matt23:7\">MAT 23:1–23:7</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:38-Mark12:39\">MRK 12:38–12:39</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke20:45-Luke20:46\">LUK 20:45–20:46</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom2:17-Rom2:27\">ROM 2:17–2:27</a></p>\n<h3>Self-justification occurs through legalism</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:25-Luke10:29\">LUK 10:25–10:29</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:1-Gal3:5\">GAL 3:1–3:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:4\">GAL 5:4</a></p>\n<h2>Self-justification causes separation from God and Jesus Christ</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:4\">GAL 5:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt18:21-Matt18:35\">MAT 18:21–18:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:9-Luke18:14\">LUK 18:9–18:14</a></p>\n<h2>Examples of self-justification</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:8-Gen3:12\">GEN 3:8–3:12</a> <em>Adam</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod32:19-Exod32:24\">EXO 32:19–32:24</a> <em>Aaron</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam13:7-1Sam13:14\">1SA 13:7–13:14</a> <em>Saul</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt19:16-Matt19:22\">MAT 19:16–19:22</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:17-Mark10:22\">MRK 10:17–10:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:18-Luke18:23\">LUK 18:18–18:23</a> <em>the rich young man</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil3:4-Phil3:9\">PHP 3:4–3:9</a> <em>Paul as a Pharisee</em></p>\n<h2>God's attitude to self-justification</h2>\n<h3>God's condemnation of self-justification</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom2:1-Rom2:11\">ROM 2:1–2:11</a></strong></p>\n<h3>God's punishment of self-justification</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov29:1\">PRO 29:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:8-Gen3:19\">GEN 3:8–3:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer6:19-Jer6:23\">JER 6:19–6:23</a></p>\n<h2>The true basis of justification</h2>\n<h3>People are justified by God's grace alone</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:8-Eph2:9\">EPH 2:8–2:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom3:21-Rom3:24\">ROM 3:21–3:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus2:11\">TIT 2:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus3:4-Titus3:7\">TIT 3:4–3:7</a></p>\n<h3>God accepts those who trust in his mercy without trying to justify themselves</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps130:3-Ps130:4\">PSA 130:3–130:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps143:2\">PSA 143:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:9-Luke18:14\">LUK 18:9–18:14</a></p>",
